# SPENNY Desktop Interaction Templates

This directory should contain PNG files for UI element detection. The following templates are required:

1. `review_button.png` - Template for the review button
2. `submit_order.png` - Template for the submit order button
3. `market_order.png` - Template for market order selection
4. `limit_order.png` - Template for limit order selection
5. `buy_button.png` - Template for buy action
6. `sell_button.png` - Template for sell action

## Template Creation Guidelines

1. Capture UI elements at 100% zoom level
2. Use a clean, unobstructed view of the element
3. Save as PNG with transparent background if possible
4. Name files exactly as specified above

## Troubleshooting

If templates are not loading:
1. Verify file names match exactly (case-sensitive)
2. Ensure PNG format
3. Check image quality and clarity
4. Verify screen recording permissions are granted

## Environment Configuration

You can override the default templates path by setting the `TEMPLATES_PATH` environment variable in your `.env` file:

```
TEMPLATES_PATH=/path/to/custom/templates
```
